sem

Class SEMscope

  • java.lang.Object
    • sem.SEMscope

  • public class SEMscope
extends java.lang.Object
    Handles scope for the semantic anaylsis of C Minus it employs a hash table to store and lookup symbols as they are created

    • Field Detail

      • parent

        public SEMscope parent
        The parent scope of the current scope

      • SymbolTable

        public java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,Descriptor> SymbolTable
        The Symbol table holds a name and its corresponding Descriptor.

        Its used to lookup symbols to see if they exist in the current scope.

      • in_block

        public boolean in_block
        Boolean flag used to prevent nested function declarations

      • return_exist

        public boolean return_exist
        Boolean flag used to prevent multiple return statements within a scope. Is true if there is already a return statement inside this scope

      • return_type

        public ASTtype return_type
        return_type is used to keep track of the first return statement's expression type to make sure returns in a scope return the same type.

        ex: if(x==1){ return 5} else {return void;} is invalid because not all paths retunr the same type.

      • main_found

        public boolean main_found
        Used to remember if main function has been defined and prevent defining main multiple times.
